{
  "essence": "Generalizing masked-prediction pretraining to diverse structured or continuous modalities fails when the masking unit, corruption process, and prediction target misalign with the modality’s inductive structure, yielding weak or biased learning signals and high sensitivity to objective design.",
  "paraphrases": {
    "LLM_NLP": "Masked language modeling is brittle when span masking and subword tokenization cut across morphemes and clauses; perplexity rises at longer context length because the corruption distribution leaks shortcut tokens and destabilizes conditioning across decoding steps.",
    "MULTIMODAL": "In vision–language pretraining, cross-modal masked modeling fails when visual token dropout disrupts cross-modal alignment with captions; VQA accuracy declines as masking ratio and image embedding granularity mis-specify which regions the text should supervise.",
    "CV": "In dense vision, masked reconstruction pretraining degrades when patch token masking ignores object boundaries; segmentation mask quality drops because feature map reconstruction within a limited receptive field overemphasizes low-frequency content given the chosen masking ratio.",
    "RL": "In reinforcement learning, masked trajectory modeling fails when the masked unit and target favor local dynamics over the reward signal; policy learning becomes brittle because reconstruction across a rollout horizon neglects value function structure under off-policy trajectories.",
    "IR_REC": "In retrieval, self-supervised span masking on queries or documents is misaligned with ranking: query-document scoring and recall@k suffer because masking granularity and targets do not shape the embedding index for discriminative reranking over a large candidate pool.",
    "SPEECH": "In speech, masked acoustic modeling fails when acoustic frame masking disrupts phoneme alignment and prosody; WER increases because the spectrogram corruption process and prediction targets mismatch temporal dependencies.",
    "ROBOTICS": "In robotics, masked pretraining over the sensorimotor loop is brittle when masking segments of sensor streams or actions ignores contact reasoning and the dynamics model; manipulation policy transfer degrades because reconstruction objectives do not capture sim-to-real variability."
  }
